Now, I haven't had braces for a VERY LONG TIME. But I just passed by Dr. Brodsky's office the other day and reminisced about those old days being a brace face (haha just kidding...sort of!)

I am absolutely terrified of orthodontists and dentists. I have traumatizing memories of evil men yanking teeth out of my mouth and telling me I had to pull more out to get braces. Then I found Dr. Brodsky. I remember him and the staff ALWAYS being super friendly and answering every question I had for them. I never had to wait long to be seen and I was in and out pretty quickly.

There was this unofficial "club" of Dr. Brodsky patients my area. He gives out shirts with a colorful version of his logo and though I'd never be caught dead in public with it on, I'd occasionally spot a few at school and we'd sort of have this unspoken brotherhood. Okay, not really...but it was funny seeing how "hip" Dr. Brodsky was - seriously, an orthodontist has to be pretty damn good to be considered "cool" among students.
